.Dd March 24, 2026
.Dt KG 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm kg
.Nd a small text editor with Emacs keybindings
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a minimal terminal text editor with Emacs-style keybindings.
It supports syntax highlighting for many programming languages,
multiple buffers, split windows, incremental search, a kill ring,
and undo/redo.
.Pp
.Nm
does not depend on curses; it uses VT100 escape sequences directly.
.Pp
If no files are given,
.Nm
opens a scratch buffer.
Multiple files each open in their own buffer.
.Sh KEY BINDINGS
.Ss Navigation
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-f / \&\(-> Ta Move forward one character
.It C-b / \&\(<- Ta Move backward one character
.It C-n / \(da Ta Move to next line
.It C-p / \(ua Ta Move to previous line
.It C-a / Home Ta Move to beginning of line
.It C-e / End Ta Move to end of line
.It C-v / PgDn Ta Scroll down one page
.It M-v / PgUp Ta Scroll up one page
.It M-f / C-\(-> Ta Move forward one word
.It M-b / C-\(<- Ta Move backward one word
.It C-\(ua Ta Move to previous paragraph
.It C-\(da Ta Move to next paragraph
.It C-Home Ta Move to beginning of buffer
.It C-End Ta Move to end of buffer
.It M-g Ta Go to line (prompts for line or line:col)
.El
.Ss Editing
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It Enter Ta Insert newline with auto-indent
.It Tab Ta Insert tab (with bracket autocomplete)
.It Backspace Ta Delete character before point
.It Delete Ta Delete character at point
.It C-d Ta Delete character before point
.It C-k Ta Kill from point to end of line
.El
.Pp
.Ic C-k
at end of line joins it with the next line (Emacs behavior).
Killed text is appended to the kill ring when
.Ic C-k
commands are consecutive.
.Ss Copy and Paste
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-Space Ta Set mark at point
.It C-w Ta Kill region (cut to kill ring)
.It M-w Ta Copy region (copy to kill ring)
.It C-y Ta Yank from kill ring (paste)
.El
.Pp
Set the mark with
.Ic C-Space ,
move the cursor to define the region, then cut with
.Ic C-w
or copy with
.Ic M-w .
Paste anywhere with
.Ic C-y .
The kill ring is shared across all buffers.
.Ss Search
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-s Ta Incremental search forward
.It C-r Ta Incremental search backward
.El
.Pp
While searching:
type to extend the query;
.Ic C-s
or
.Ic \(->
or
.Ic \(da
finds the next match;
.Ic C-r
or
.Ic \(<-
or
.Ic \(ua
finds the previous match;
.Ic Enter
accepts the match;
.Ic Esc
cancels and returns to the original position;
.Ic Backspace
removes the last character from the query.
.Ss Undo
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-_ / C-/ Ta Undo last change
.El
.Pp
Undo history is per-buffer.
Each buffer keeps up to 1000 operations.
The buffer is marked unmodified when undo returns to the last-saved state.
.Ss File and Buffer Commands
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-x C-s Ta Save current buffer
.It C-x s Ta Save all modified buffers
.It C-x C-f Ta Open file in new buffer
.It C-x C-r Ta Open file read-only in new buffer
.It C-x C-q Ta Toggle read-only mode on current buffer
.It C-x b Ta Switch to buffer (interactive)
.It C-x k Ta Kill (close) current buffer
.It C-x C-b Ta Open buffer list
.It C-x C-c Ta Quit
.El
.Ss Window Commands
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-x 2 Ta Split window horizontally
.It C-x 3 Ta Split window vertically
.It C-x o Ta Switch to next window
.It C-x 0 Ta Delete current window
.It C-x 1 Ta Delete all other windows
.El
.Ss Utility
.Bl -column "C-Home / C-End" "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX" -compact
.It Sy Key Ta Sy Action
.It C-g Ta Cancel current operation
.It C-l Ta Redraw screen
.It C-h Ta Toggle built-in help screen
.El
.Sh BUFFERS
.Nm
supports up to 20 open buffers.
Each buffer has its own undo history, dirty flag, and read-only state.
Special system buffers (such as the buffer list) have names enclosed in
.Sq *
and can be closed with
.Ic q .
.Pp
The kill ring is global and shared across all buffers, so text killed in
one buffer can be yanked in another.
.Sh WINDOWS
The terminal can be divided into multiple windows with
.Ic C-x 2
(horizontal split) or
.Ic C-x 3
(vertical split).
Each window shows one buffer and maintains its own scroll position and cursor.
Multiple windows may show the same buffer.
Use
.Ic C-x o
to cycle between windows.
Up to 8 windows may be open simultaneously.
.Sh SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
Syntax is detected automatically from the file extension.
Supported languages include:
C, C++, Python, Shell, JavaScript, TypeScript, Rust, Java, C#,
PHP, Ruby, Swift, SQL, Dart, HTML, JSX, Vue, Angular, Svelte, Makefile, and Markdown.
Hash-bang lines
.Pq #!
are used as a fallback when the extension is not recognised.
.Sh AUTOCOMPLETE
.Nm
automatically inserts matching closing brackets when an opening bracket is
typed, provided the cursor is at the end of a line.
Recognised pairs are
.Sq () ,
.Sq [] ,
and
.Sq {} .
Autocomplete is suppressed when text arrives quickly, such as during a paste
operation.
.Sh GOTO LINE
.Ic M-g
prompts for a line number, optionally followed by a colon and a column
number
.Pq e.g. Ar 42:10 .
The cursor is moved to that position and the view is centred vertically.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Nm
uses the controlling terminal
.Pa /dev/tty
for raw-mode input and output.
Terminal size changes
.Pq SIGWINCH
are handled gracefully.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa /dev/tty
Terminal device used for raw-mode I/O.
.El
